            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><ab><lb n="1"/>
                Pro salute commili<supplied reason="lost"><expan><abbr>ton</abbr><ex>um</ex></expan></supplied> <lb n="2"/>Fortun<supplied reason="lost">ae</supplied> <lb n="3"/>sacrum <lb n="4"/>Cassius <lb n="5"/>Troianu<supplied reason="lost">s</supplied> <lb n="6"/>|(centurio) <expan><abbr>Brit</abbr><ex>tonum</ex></expan> Mur<supplied reason="lost"><expan><abbr>r</abbr><ex>ensium</ex></expan></supplied> <lb n="7"/><expan><abbr>v</abbr><ex>otum</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>s</abbr><ex>olvit</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>l</abbr><ex>ibens</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>l</abbr><ex>aetus</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>m</abbr><ex>erito</ex></expan>
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>In 2 Teile gebrochen; auf der corona eine Mondsichel. Z. 1 möglicherweise nachträglich eingefügt. (B): CIL XIII: Haug - Sixt: Z. 1: commili[tonum]; Haug - Sixt: Z. 4: [C]assiu[s]; Z. 6: Mu[rr(ensium)?]; Schmidt Heidenreich: Z. 4: Troianus. Autopsie R. Wiegels. Funddatum: zwischen 1828 und 1835.</p>
            </div>
